tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, indicating impaired glucose metabolism or possible prediabetes. Creatinine and total cholesterol are slightly below the reference range but are not clinically concerning in isolation. Other parameters, including glucose, renal function, electrolytes, and lipid profile, are within normal limits. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected; recommend monitoring glycemic control.
